import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='state', y='rate', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of rate across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('State')
    plt.ylabel('Rate')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
